    <text id="B0560T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How forwards a claim by a man named Robert Brick, and asks for more information
                    about how to assist freedmen submitting claims for losses sustained during the
                    war.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Clerk of the Court of Claims<lb/>Washington, D.C.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-02-12"><abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> 12th 1866</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The accompanying claim has been handed me by <hi rend="underline">Robert
                    Brick</hi> a Freedman, to be forwarded as it now is, but I have as yet been
                    unable to learn anything concerning claims of Freedpeople previously forwarded.</p>

                <p>I should be glad to <del hand="h1">learn</del> receive any information that would
                    tend to assist the Freedmen in obtaining compensation for losses sustained by
                    them.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, Sir &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>W. Storer How<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
